                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35143",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fromvega",
                        "name": "fromvega",
                        "displayName": "Luiz A Brandao Jr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It indeed needs to be corrected. I just noticed that after getting errors from the load script.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fromvega",
                        "name": "fromvega",
                        "displayName": "Luiz A Brandao Jr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-09T12:01:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-09T12:01:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35144",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Um.... the directory structure is this:\n{code}\nquickstart\/\n|-- application\/\n|-- data\/\n|   |-- db\/\n{code}\nThis is the recommended project directory structure per our manual. As such, having the following configuration:\n{code}\nresources.db.params.dbname = APPLICATION_PATH \"\/..\/data\/db\/guestbook.db\"\n{code}\nis correct. I've also tested it, and the code works correctly.\n\nClosing as non-reproducible.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-09T12:21:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-09T12:21:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35371",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fromvega",
                        "name": "fromvega",
                        "displayName": "Luiz A Brandao Jr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, the path is correct if you put your data directory outside the application directory, but the problem is in this paragraph where it states that the data directory is INSIDE the application directory:\r\n\r\n\"At this point we have a connection to a database; in our case, its a connection to a Sqlite database located inside our application\/data\/  directory. So, let's design a simple table that will hold our guestbook entries.\"",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fromvega",
                        "name": "fromvega",
                        "displayName": "Luiz A Brandao Jr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-17T15:37:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-17T15:37:19.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
